INSERT INTO `news` VALUES ('40', '7', 'People think Beyonce and Jay-Z\'s son\'s name proves an old conspiracy theory', 'Beyoncé and Jay-Z\'s newly born twins have been in the world for one month now but their names have been kept private.\r\nNow the superstar couple have revealed the children\'s names to be Sir Carter and Rumi and did so via the most amazing Instagram post you\'ve ever seen (since the last Beyoncé Instagram post).', 'images/image-38.jpg', '2017-07-15 12:54:25', null, 'post/40', 'images/postimages/image-38.jpg');
INSERT INTO `news` VALUES ('41', '7', 'The biggest volcano in Europe is on fire, and now things are starting to get really freaky', 'There are multiple fires burning on Mount Vesuvius – and it looks rather terrifying.\r\n\r\nThe volcano isn’t erupting – thankfully – but it is host to multiple wildfires near Naples, Italy.\r\n\r\nWildfires are causing evacuations in nearby towns and villages and tourists are being warned to stay away while firefighters attempt to tackle the blazes. \r\n\r\nThe pictures emerging from the region are striking.\r\n\r\n    #vesuvio #napoli #fuoco #protezionecivile pic.twitter.com/yCeWPq87k4\r\n    — di fiore fotografi (@fotodifiore) July 11, 2017\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n    #Vesuvio on #fire view from #Pompei pic.twitter.com/hRgoHRHvDp\r\n    — Rossella Luciani (@rosscaracol) July 11, 2017', 'images/image-39.jpg', '2017-07-15 12:54:33', null, 'post/41', 'images/postimages/image-39.jpg');
INSERT INTO `news` VALUES ('42', '7', 'Ryan Reynolds had the best response to Wonder Woman beating Deadpool at the box office', 'You may have noticed that superhero movies are making a lot of money at the moment.\r\n\r\nWhether it is Marvel\'s Avengers or DC\'s Batman and Superman, the comic book adaptations are packing out cinema screens all year round. \r\n\r\nOne of this year\'s biggest successes is DC\'s Wonder Woman, starring Gal Gadot as the empowering Amazonian Princess.', 'images/image-40.jpg', '2017-07-15 12:54:40', null, 'post/42', 'images/postimages/image-40.jpg');
INSERT INTO `news` VALUES ('43', '7', 'Macron got a little NSFW with his wife during the Trump\'s visit', 'French president Emmanuel Macron has shown the world he is passionate about much more than politics.\r\n\r\nDuring a state visit by American President Donald Trump and First Lady Melania Trump, Macron and his wife Brigitte decided to take the pair on a tour of the historic complex of buildings Les Invalides in Paris.\r\n\r\nIt was during this tour of museums and monuments, which include a church marking the final resting place of Napoleon Bonaparte, Macron reportedly gave his wife a “tap on the read end”.\r\n\r\nThe \'rear-end tap\' was allegedly spotted by pool reporter Brian Bennett, and later tweeted out by the White House reporter for the New York Times Maggie Haberman. \r\n\r\nMr Macron\'s wife reportedly “looked surprised and smiled”.', 'images/image-41.jpg', '2017-07-15 12:54:47', null, 'post/43', 'images/postimages/image-41.jpg');
INSERT INTO `news` VALUES ('44', '7', 'Theresa May has been PM exactly one year - she\'s never had it so bad', 'On 18 April Theresa May threw away the first majority won by the Conservative Party in 23 years.\r\n\r\nThe joy of being in power, and without the help of the Liberal Democrats, was smothered after just 1 year, 11 months, and 11 days.\r\n\r\n13 July marks the first year of her premiership, after she replaced David Cameron - the leader who\'d won that majority.\r\n\r\nWhen she first ascended, things were looking great.\r\n\r\nHow things have changed.', 'images/image-42.jpg', '2017-07-15 12:54:55', null, 'post/44', 'images/postimages/image-42.jpg');
INSERT INTO `news` VALUES ('45', '7', 'Donald Trump yanks arm of French President Emmanuel Macron\'s wife in latest bizarre handshake', 'United States President Donald Trump has a thing about handshakes. \r\n\r\nWe\'ve covered it before. World leaders know it\'s a thing. They\'ve got strategies against it now.\r\n\r\nTrump and his wife, Melania, are visiting France to mark Bastille Day, taking Emmanuel Macron up on his surprise invitation.\r\n\r\nThe last time he publicly shook hands with the newly elected French President, Macron definitely got the better of the 45th President.', 'images/image-43.jpg', '2017-07-15 12:55:02', null, 'post/45', 'images/postimages/image-43.jpg');
INSERT INTO `news` VALUES ('46', '7', 'Map reveals if you\'re living in one of the laziest countries in the world', 'Scientists at Stanford University have analysed 68 million days\' worth of data from people\'s smartphones to study physical activity on a global scale.\r\n\r\nMore than 700,000 people across 46 countries were part of the study, published in the journal Nature, whose activity on the Argus fitness app was monitored.\r\n\r\nHong Kong was the most active of the countries by step count (an average of 6,880 a day) and it also had the smallest \'activity inequality\' (a score of 22.2).\r\n\r\n\'Activity inequality\' was the difference in activity between the fittest and the laziest.\r\n\r\nBy \'activity inequality\', China placed second (24.5), followed by Sweden (24.6), South Korea (24.7), and the Czech Republic (24.8). The UK ranked 36th by this measure with a score of 28.8.\r\n\r\nSaudi Arabia was the least equal by activity, with a score of 32.5.', 'images/image-44.jpg', '2017-07-15 12:55:08', null, 'post/46', 'images/postimages/image-44.jpg');
INSERT INTO `news` VALUES ('47', '7', 'Man takes his feud with a neighbour all the way to Google Earth', 'Neighbourly disputes are always awkward – but this paticular tiff has gone next-level.\r\n\r\nProblems started between Brian Juel and his neighbours Cindy and Brian Zechenelly when Cindy built a garage apartment on her property in 2009 and painted it purple. Oh yes, this goes way back.\r\n\r\nCindy told the Peninsula Daily News that her primary inspiration for the purple came from the Painted Ladies, tricolor Victorian houses on Alamo Square in San Francisco.\r\n\r\nJuel, who petitioned against the purple creation, told the same publication:', 'images/image-45.jpg', '2017-07-15 12:55:16', null, 'post/47', 'images/postimages/image-45.jpg');
INSERT INTO `news` VALUES ('48', '7', 'This is the kind of behaviour that will make people think you\'re stupid ', 'If you don’t want people to think you’re stupid, you should stop trying to do things above your station, according to science.\r\n\r\nResearchers have collected news stories containing descriptions of \'stupid\' behaviour, and also asked 26 students to keep a five-day diary of any incidents they saw of people acting \'stupidly\'.\r\n\r\nThese diary entries were shown to 154 other students, who were then asked to rate how stupid each event was, and rate how different psychological factors were to blame (such as tiredness or overconfidence).\r\n\r\nThe researchers found there are three main types of stupid. So, here\'s what not to do if you want to avoid looking stupid. \r\n1. Confident ignorance\r\n\r\nThis is when people do something risky when they lack the required skills or knowledge.\r\n\r\nFor example; don\'t say you can ice skate when you absolutely know you cannot ice skate.\r\n2. Lack of control\r\n\r\nThis stems from obsessive or addictive behaviour.\r\n3. Absentmindedness\r\n\r\nThis is when people fail to do something properly because they lack practical skills, or were distracted. \r\n\r\nIn other words, a Friday afternoon in the office. ', 'images/image-46.jpg', '2017-07-15 12:55:23', null, 'post/48', 'images/postimages/image-46.jpg');
INSERT INTO `news` VALUES ('49', '7', 'Super train that would speed between cities at 700mph has its first successful test', 'The concept of a \'hyperloop\', a rail system that works in a vacuum tube and thus reaches very high speeds, has been a pipe dream for a while now.\r\n\r\nElon Musk mentioned the concept back in 2012 and liked its immunity to weather, speed and low power consumption.\r\n\r\nThe speeds of such creations, which some analyses suggest could reach up to 760mph, would reduce a 6 hour journey by car to 35 minutes - even quicker than a flight, which currently takes around 1 hour and 20 minutes.\r\n\r\nNow, one of the startups working on this transportation system, just shared footage of their first full-scale test in a vacuum.', 'images/image-47.jpg', '2017-07-15 12:55:30', null, 'post/49', 'images/postimages/image-47.jpg');
INSERT INTO `news` VALUES ('50', '18', 'Nominees revealed for 2013 Laureus World Sports Awards ', 'After the unforgettable Olympic year, it comes as no surprise that many gold medallists from the London Games are up for Laureus Awards. ', 'images/image-48.jpg', '2017-07-15 12:55:38', null, 'post/50', 'images/postimages/image-48.jpg');
